### Deploy Workloads on Destination Cluster

Use the release branch identified in the [Release Branch for Workload Deployments](#release-branch-for-workload-deployments) prerequisite step.

**Deploy workloads (main stacks):**

- **Pipeline:** [Deploy Stack #333](https://dev.azure.com/hmcts-cpp/cpp-apps/_build?definitionId=333)

This pipeline deploys the following namespaces per stack:

- `ns-<env>-ccm-<stack>`
- `ns-<env>-idam-<stack>`
- `ns-<env>-cdns-<stack>`
- `ns-<env>-web-<stack>`

**Deploy Alfapp workloads:**

For `ns-<env>-alfapp-<stack>` namespaces, use a separate pipeline:

- **Pipeline:** [Deploy Alfapp #181](https://dev.azure.com/hmcts-cpp/cpp-apps/_build?definitionId=181&_a=summary)

For detailed instructions on deploying to AKS, refer to the [Deploy to AKS](https://tools.hmcts.net/confluence/spaces/EI/pages/1525460437/Deploy+to+AKS) guide.
